<h3 id="isr-rate-table" sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/localizations/latam-mex-isr-declaration-report-supporting-processes.md" sourcestartlinenumber="56">ISR rate table</h3>
<p sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/localizations/latam-mex-isr-declaration-report-supporting-processes.md" sourcestartlinenumber="58">You can create or update the ISR rates that are used to calculate the provisional ISR payment amount. In general, this table is available on the government site. You identify the year and month, and then the minimum and maximum amounts, the fixed amount, and the ISR rate. In the ISR payment report, the rate percentage is used to multiply the derived value after the minimum amount is deducted from the resulting fiscal amount. <strong sourcefile="ProcessDoku/02_SupportProcesses/02_01_Finance/localizations/latam-mex-isr-declaration-report-supporting-processes.md" sourcestartlinenumber="58">Example</strong></p>
